snippet.textDisplay:
To any fans of Danplan, this is not a personal attack on Dsn, rather something to show you all and hopefully Dan a better understanding of this situation.

First, I would like for Dan to realize that by becoming a "boss" or "employer" of your own friend already had a way of destroying your friendship. Second, to say that Stephen had no part in helping to grown the channel and giving him less then 1% is awful. When you have under 100 employees (I believe that Danplan would probably have less then 50) you dont pay everyone equally. Since Stephen had such a big part in Danplan and had such a large part in its success, he should get a raise, like an employee that you claimed him to be. Third, you should have been able to find a solution thats fits the both of you and Dan should have found a way to solve this problem.

Due to Dan being inconsiderate to one of the hardest working "employees" on this channel, he has lost that hard worker, a hilarious piece to a now unfinished puzzle. I cant help but feel bad for Hosha and feel angry at Dan. Hosha is caught in something that he probably doesnt want to be in.

So the last thing I will ever say on this channels comment section is, Dan, you made a huge mistake tactically, one that will most definitely shatter this channel and you may loose a lot of subscribers. One of those subscribers is me, and I am positive I am not the only one.
